In the case of those who had the longer index than the risk yearbook, however, 33 per cent fell, for men before 60 years the risk reduction reached 87 per cent.
The length of the two fingers - formed during the prenatal period - indicates, among other things, different levels of sexual hormones to which the child is exposed in the uterus.
