The European Union changes the rules for obtaining the visa
People must go to the Visa Applicants Service Centres prior to their interview in the Consular Section; the cost of waiting will be reduced.
With effect from 10 January 2011, the procedure for processing visas at the United States Embassy and consulates will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to submit themselves to the Visa Applicants Service Centres (ASC) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The ASC staff will take the applicant's biometric information, which will be revised by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will have some advantages for the aspirants, including the following:
The total cost of treating the visa will be lower, no longer will be necessary to make a payment for a meeting, another payment for the treatment of the visa and another for the mail service to deliver the document.
The aspirant will make a unique payment that will cover the three services.
The current rate will remain the same: $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visas on request (including visas for temporary workers) and $390 for traders and investors visas.
Persons wishing to renew their visas will not have to present themselves for an interview with the Consular Representative, they will only present themselves to the closer ASC where they will present the documents and be printed.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be taken into the ASC, applicants wishing to meet for a second meeting to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain there less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants to the Consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra $26 duty rate.
For further information on the new procedure for requesting visa, please visit the following page: http://mexico.usebassy.gov/bolettines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
